&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oncology Receptionist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity has arisen for a 37.5 hour full time Band 2 Oncology Ward Clerk/Receptionist within the Oncology Department at North Middlesex University Hospital NHS Trust. Working in the Oncology Department, the successful candidate will have a real opportunity to improve the care and experience of patients going through cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should be flexible with regards to working occasional late shifts, with good IT skills, and experience in filing and other clerical duties. Main responsibilities include the management of clinic schedules and appointment bookings, recording patient outcomes, and providing a friendly and helpful front desk service. Excellent communication skills are necessary and the ability to work as part of a dedicated team. Previous experience of office or reception duties is essential, preferably within the healthcare setting, and all candidates must meet the criteria laid out within the person specification included in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this post may close earlier than the advertised date due to high numbers of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHafza AbdirahmanJob titleDeputy Service ManagerEmail addresshafza.abdirahman@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Hafza Abdirahman, Deputy Service Manager - Oncology &amp; Palliative Care on 0208 887 3382.&lt;/p&gt;
